<plot>The ninth entry, based on the radio program, of the 1940-41 production season (RKO production number 24201) finds the regular panel staff---Oscar Levant, Franklin P. Adams and John Kiewan---aided by writer and radio-commentator Elmer Davis in coming up with the correct (often) or incorrect (sometimes, especially if Levant went out of his way to find a caustic comment)answers to the questions posed by the show-host and moderator Clifton Fadiman.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?264913</url></doc>
